tip.text: The taiyaki is nice but the crepe is abit hard to eat~ Recommend to get the custard filling
Red velvet waffles is a must try with its cream cheese in between the waffles! Ice cream flavours is great too! $10 combo w drinks is totally worth it ^^
Great ambience with wide range of books.If you are keen on SG based books here is the right place to go!
Interesting train playground with one of the three merry-go-round left in Singapore!
Really good cupcakes and wide variety of desserts! GofrostSg situated at Wednesday Cafe is also really great! Banana chocolate ice cream flavour is a must try!
Oreo,red bean & sweet potato patbingsu are super good!! Really love nutella toast as it was a great mix of warmth( rice cake inside the toast) and cold (ice cream) and super friendly staffs!
Cheese fries are undeniably good and the subs are delicious!
Butterbeer drink was great! Vanilla Waffle with salted caramel sauce was delicious but a bit sweet~ Coffee waffle with espresso butterscotch sauce was delightful! Must try for coffee lovers!
Super delicious naan and pratas! Chicken curry is alright~~ overall really delicious!
Really good mozzarella cheese and wedges!! Chicken is cooked well but the sauce is a bit too  tangy and sour to personal preference.Really easy to find access too so overall very good!^^
Wonderful Patbingsu esp the Choco banana Patbingsu and Oreo Patbingsu!! Quite hard to get here but worth the effort
Awesome service! Very little space but came on weekdays so it was not crowded.The morning run is delicious and so is the cinnamon cappucino and the berry pancakes!! Awesome in overall
Nice milkshake! Pancakes stuffed with leek and cheese are average! Overall quite pleasing :)
